WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:04.254
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.337 --> 00:05.296
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.380 --> 00:07.632
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.716 --> 00:09.300
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:09.384 --> 00:11.177
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:11.261 --> 00:13.596
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:13.680 --> 00:14.889
<i>- ♪ In the Loud House ♪</i>

00:14.973 --> 00:16.599
<i>♪ In the Loud House ♪</i>

00:16.683 --> 00:18.101
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:18.184 --> 00:19.978
<i>♪ It's how we show our love ♪</i>

00:20.061 --> 00:21.479
<i>- ♪ In the Loud House,</i>
<i>in the Loud House ♪</i>

00:21.563 --> 00:23.148
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:23.231 --> 00:24.524
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.607 --> 00:27.861
<i>- ♪ Loud, Loud, Loud ♪</i>

00:27.944 --> 00:28.528
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud House ♪</i>

00:28.611 --> 00:30.488
{\an7}- Poo-poo.

00:32.031 --> 00:34.951
<i>[exciting music]</i>

00:35.034 --> 00:39.748
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:39.831 --> 00:41.624
<i>- And that's why I propose</i>

00:41.708 --> 00:44.878
we cryogenically freeze Luan
for April Fool's Day.

00:44.961 --> 00:47.505
She can't prank us
if she's frozen solid.

00:47.589 --> 00:51.134
Oh, come on.
She'll maintain brain function.

00:51.217 --> 00:53.094
Well, a little.

00:53.178 --> 00:54.637
- Lana and I have an idea.

00:54.721 --> 00:57.432
[wheels squeaking]

00:57.515 --> 01:00.143
{\an1}We call it
the Prank-Me-Not Poncho.

01:00.226 --> 01:01.978
{\an1}The inflatable lining
cushions you

01:02.061 --> 01:04.063
from all manner of pranks.

01:04.147 --> 01:05.190
- Ow!

01:05.272 --> 01:07.192
Ooh! Ow!
I can feel that.

01:07.275 --> 01:09.903
{\an1}- Not a problem.
We just need a little more air.

01:12.238 --> 01:15.784
- Does anyone have an idea
that'll actually work?

01:15.867 --> 01:17.285
April Fool's Day
is this weekend,

01:17.368 --> 01:19.412
and I am not losing
another eyebrow.

01:19.496 --> 01:21.247
They're starting to
grow in coarse.

01:21.331 --> 01:24.667
- I say we post bad reviews
of Fanny's Prank Emporium

01:24.751 --> 01:26.669
and force them
out of business.

01:26.753 --> 01:28.213
- Ooh, that's good.

01:28.296 --> 01:30.298
We eliminate her supplier,
we eliminate the problem.

01:30.381 --> 01:31.883
- We're too late for that.

01:31.966 --> 01:33.426
Luan got her prank supplies

01:33.510 --> 01:36.262
shipped to an offshore warehouse
months ago.

01:36.346 --> 01:37.806
She told me that to scare me.

01:37.889 --> 01:39.140
It totally worked.

01:39.224 --> 01:41.267
{\an1}- Leni, are you
even paying attention?

01:41.351 --> 01:42.602
- Oh, sorry, I was just

01:42.685 --> 01:44.354
reading this ad
for a clown camp

01:44.437 --> 01:46.606
{\an3}that takes place over
April Fool's Day Weekend.

01:46.689 --> 01:48.566
all: What?

01:48.650 --> 01:50.026
- This is perfect!

01:50.109 --> 01:51.611
If we send Luan to this camp,

01:51.694 --> 01:53.029
she'll be two states
away from us.

01:53.112 --> 01:57.700
Oh, but it costs 500 bucks.

01:57.784 --> 01:59.077
- Well, that is a lot of money,

01:59.160 --> 02:01.454
{\an1}but if it means
we don't have

02:01.538 --> 02:02.872
{\an1}to spend April Fool's
in these suits,

02:02.956 --> 02:04.374
I'd say it's worth it.

02:04.457 --> 02:07.335
{\an3}- Agreed.
Someone toss me my checkbook.

02:07.418 --> 02:10.170
- A weekend at
Funny Farm's Clown Camp?

02:10.255 --> 02:13.007
Oh!
This is my dream come true!

02:13.091 --> 02:14.926
Oh, thank you,
thank you, thank you!

02:15.009 --> 02:17.011
But what's the occasion?

02:17.095 --> 02:18.680
- Why do we need an occasion

02:18.763 --> 02:22.016
{\an3}to spoil our favorite
little comedienne, huh?

02:22.100 --> 02:25.603
{\an1}- Oh, wait.
It's on April Fool's weekend.

02:25.687 --> 02:27.856
- Is it?
I, uh--I didn't realize.

02:27.939 --> 02:29.649
- I don't know if I can be away
from my family

02:29.732 --> 02:31.276
on my favorite holiday.

02:31.359 --> 02:32.986
{\an1}- Ah, but think about
all that fresh meat at the camp

02:33.069 --> 02:35.530
just waiting to be pranked.

02:35.613 --> 02:37.407
- Oh, you're right!

02:37.490 --> 02:40.118
Well, in that case,
I "camp" wait.

02:40.201 --> 02:42.036
[laughs] Get it?

02:42.120 --> 02:44.247
- Oh, that is hilarious!
- That's good!

02:44.330 --> 02:45.957
- Where do you come up
with this stuff?

02:46.040 --> 02:48.084
Oh, I swear,
I'm gonna pee.

02:48.167 --> 02:50.503
{\an3}- Lincoln,
don't oversell it.

02:50.587 --> 02:52.547
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

02:52.630 --> 02:55.592
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:55.675 --> 02:57.510
- Well, guys, this is it.

02:57.594 --> 02:59.220
I'm really gonna miss you, but--

02:59.304 --> 03:01.097
- Bye!
- See ya!

03:01.180 --> 03:03.391
{\an1}- Wait, wait!
I changed my mind!

03:03.474 --> 03:04.809
- Punch it, Dad!

03:04.893 --> 03:06.436
[all scream]

03:06.519 --> 03:09.105
- I want the blue clown shoes,
not the pink ones.

03:09.188 --> 03:10.356
[all sigh]

03:10.440 --> 03:12.191
- Here, take them all.

03:12.275 --> 03:14.485
- Take mine, too,
just to be safe.

03:14.569 --> 03:16.446
<i>[all cheering]</i>

03:19.741 --> 03:21.701
[engine rattling, pops]

03:21.784 --> 03:23.369
<i>- Oh, dang it.</i>

03:23.453 --> 03:26.289
{\an3}Sorry, guys, looks like
Vanzilla just died on us.

03:26.372 --> 03:27.957
- I'm on it, Dad.

03:28.041 --> 03:30.585
Huh, that's weird.

03:30.668 --> 03:32.378
I thought I packed my toolbox.

03:32.462 --> 03:33.671
- It's okay, sweetie.

03:33.755 --> 03:34.339
{\an1}We'll just get a tow
in the morning.

03:34.422 --> 03:36.382
There's a motel right there.

03:36.466 --> 03:37.800
- [scoffs]

03:37.884 --> 03:41.304
Lola Loud does not
stay in two-star motels.

03:41.387 --> 03:42.430
[glass breaks]

03:42.513 --> 03:43.723
- Well, there you go.

03:43.806 --> 03:46.559
{\an1}Now it's a one-star,
so you're good.

03:46.643 --> 03:49.312
{\an1}- And please watch over
Cliff, Charles, Geo, and Walt,

03:49.395 --> 03:52.982
{\an1}and Izzy, Hops, Bitey,
Fangs, El Diablo--

03:53.066 --> 03:54.317
{\an3}- Lana.

03:54.400 --> 03:56.319
{\an1}- But I didn't get to
my ant colony yet.

03:56.402 --> 03:56.903
- Good night.

03:56.986 --> 04:00.907
[insect chirping]

04:03.326 --> 04:04.577
{\an8}- Seriously?

04:04.661 --> 04:06.579
{\an8}That's not bothering
anyone else?

04:06.663 --> 04:08.164
{\an8}- Oh, my bad.

04:08.247 --> 04:09.999
{\an8}Those gas station burritos
always get me going.

04:10.083 --> 04:13.419
{\an8}- Not that, the cricket.

04:13.503 --> 04:15.046
- Ouch!
- Seriously, dude?

04:15.129 --> 04:17.089
- I'm sorry.
I can't see anything.

04:17.173 --> 04:18.591
Let me just turn on a light.

04:18.675 --> 04:20.677
<i>[sirens blaring on TV]</i>

04:20.760 --> 04:22.053
all: Lincoln!

04:22.136 --> 04:23.221
- Sorry.

04:23.304 --> 04:24.514
[sirens blaring]

04:24.597 --> 04:26.099
[bed vibrating]
- Lincoln!

04:26.182 --> 04:27.350
{\an1}Oh!

04:27.433 --> 04:28.935
{\an8}- I'm sorry.

04:29.018 --> 04:30.812
{\an9}I can't figure out
how anything works in here.

04:30.895 --> 04:32.438
[alarm blaring]

04:32.522 --> 04:33.815
- Lincoln,
stop hitting switches.

04:33.898 --> 04:35.441
You're making things worse.

04:35.525 --> 04:37.694
Now, where is the dang plug
for this thing?

04:37.777 --> 04:39.195
Ow!

04:39.278 --> 04:41.406
{\an1}- I'll get some more towels
to clean up that coffee.

04:41.489 --> 04:41.990
{\an1}[screams]

04:42.073 --> 04:43.866
[blaring stops]

04:43.950 --> 04:46.160
- Well, that should do it.

04:46.244 --> 04:47.578
Whoever wired this place

04:47.662 --> 04:49.539
had no idea
what they were doing.

04:49.622 --> 04:52.458
{\an8}- I think they knew exactly
what they were doing.

04:52.542 --> 04:53.626
Look what I found.

04:53.710 --> 04:55.211
This cricket is a fake.

04:55.294 --> 04:56.879
It's from
Fanny's Prank Emporium.

04:56.963 --> 04:59.048
[all gasp]

04:59.132 --> 05:00.883
{\an1}- That's where Luan
gets all her supplies.

05:00.967 --> 05:03.553
- [gasps] You don't think
she's behind this, do you?

05:03.636 --> 05:05.013
{\an3}- [scoffs]
She can't be.

05:05.096 --> 05:07.682
{\an3}She's at camp.
I'll call her right now.

05:07.765 --> 05:09.392
[beep]
<i>- Hello, family.</i>

05:09.475 --> 05:11.894
<i>I hope you're</i>
<i>enjoying your stay.</i>

05:11.978 --> 05:15.857
<i>Buckle up, there's mo-telling</i>
<i>what's gonna happen next.</i>

05:15.940 --> 05:18.568
<i>[cackles] Get it?</i>

05:18.651 --> 05:19.694
[screaming]

05:19.777 --> 05:20.778
- Okay, everybody stay calm.

05:20.862 --> 05:23.322
We'll just go to the manager
and get a new room.

05:23.406 --> 05:25.074
- How do we know
that's not exactly

05:25.158 --> 05:27.035
what Luan wants us to do?

05:27.118 --> 05:28.286
I vote we stay put.

05:28.369 --> 05:29.328
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:29.412 --> 05:30.621
{\an1}[all gasp]

05:30.705 --> 05:32.707
- Hang on, Lisa.
We'll get you out.

05:32.790 --> 05:35.043
- [muffled] Negative.
Proceed without me.

05:35.126 --> 05:36.169
I'm safer in here.

05:36.252 --> 05:37.128
- Let's go.

05:37.211 --> 05:40.798
{\an8}[cricket chirping]

05:40.882 --> 05:42.884
{\an8}- [muffled] Lincoln!
The cricket!

05:42.967 --> 05:44.135
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:44.218 --> 05:46.346
- Ah!
She cut the floorboards!

05:46.429 --> 05:47.388
[wood creaks, pops]

05:47.472 --> 05:48.389
{\an1}all: Oh!

05:48.473 --> 05:50.600
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:50.683 --> 05:52.268
- Luna, grab my foot.

05:52.351 --> 05:54.437
I'll pull you to safety
with my quads.

05:54.520 --> 05:56.022
- I can't, dude.

05:56.105 --> 05:58.441
Major gelatin hands.

05:58.524 --> 05:59.525
I'm cool here.

05:59.609 --> 06:02.570
Carry on, my wayward sons!

06:02.653 --> 06:07.700
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:07.784 --> 06:09.577
all: Dibs not!

06:09.660 --> 06:11.996
{\an3}- Dang it.
I always do it wrong.

06:12.080 --> 06:13.873
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

06:13.956 --> 06:14.957
[boing]

06:15.041 --> 06:16.000
[yells]

06:16.084 --> 06:17.210
[neon humming]

06:17.293 --> 06:19.253
<i>[scary musical sting]</i>

06:19.337 --> 06:20.338
{\an1}[all gasp]

06:20.421 --> 06:22.048
You guys go on without me.

06:22.131 --> 06:25.968
I'd rather be stuck up here
than get pranked by Luan.

06:26.052 --> 06:26.969
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:27.053 --> 06:28.262
[bell dinging]

06:28.346 --> 06:29.305
- Good evening, sir.

06:29.388 --> 06:30.515
We need a new room.

06:30.598 --> 06:33.476
- Fine.
You can have 1A.

06:33.559 --> 06:35.561
- Princesses first!

06:35.645 --> 06:38.147
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:38.231 --> 06:38.940
[animal chatters,
Lola screams]

06:39.023 --> 06:40.900
[hissing]

06:40.983 --> 06:44.278
The rat skunked me.

06:44.362 --> 06:47.698
- The real 1A's over there.

06:47.782 --> 06:48.991
Don't touch that handle!

06:49.075 --> 06:50.660
Remember what happened to Leni.

06:50.743 --> 06:53.454
- Hi, you guys!

06:53.538 --> 06:55.581
- I have an idea.

06:55.665 --> 06:57.250
{\an3}Charge!

06:57.333 --> 06:58.251
{\an3}[yells]

06:58.334 --> 07:00.002
{\an3}[splat]

07:00.086 --> 07:03.339
I'm okay!
I landed in pie!

07:03.422 --> 07:04.674
{\an8}[slurps]

07:04.757 --> 07:07.218
{\an8}And of course
she made it rhubarb pie,

07:07.301 --> 07:08.886
{\an8}which I'm allergic to.

07:08.970 --> 07:10.179
- I can't take this anymore.

07:10.263 --> 07:11.264
I'm getting out of here!

07:11.347 --> 07:12.473
<i>[scary music]</i>

07:12.557 --> 07:13.850
[car beeping]
[sighs]

07:13.933 --> 07:14.976
[airbags whoosh]
[grunts]

07:15.059 --> 07:16.561
My eyebrows!

07:16.644 --> 07:18.020
{\an1}- Quick!
To the basement!

07:18.104 --> 07:20.022
{\an1}It's always the safest place
in an emergency!

07:20.106 --> 07:23.067
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

07:23.151 --> 07:24.485
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:24.569 --> 07:26.237
- [laughs]

07:26.320 --> 07:28.489
- Lily, no, it could be a trap!

07:28.573 --> 07:30.074
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:30.158 --> 07:32.618
{\an1}Oh, shoot.

07:32.702 --> 07:35.371
I'm trapped!
Save yourselves!

07:35.454 --> 07:37.290
{\an3}- Come on, kids!
Say good-bye to your mother!

07:37.373 --> 07:39.417
[click]

07:39.500 --> 07:42.044
- Please tell me
this is not bleach.

07:43.796 --> 07:45.423
And it's bleach.

07:45.506 --> 07:47.008
Go on without me.

07:47.091 --> 07:49.969
I don't want to be seen
in public like this.

07:50.052 --> 07:53.222
{\an1}- [breathing heavily]
Okay. Take a knee.

07:53.306 --> 07:55.683
{\an1}Now, I know we're
dropping like flies here.

07:55.766 --> 07:57.059
But let's not lose hope.

07:57.143 --> 07:58.644
{\an1}If we stick together,
we should be okay.

07:58.728 --> 08:01.397
{\an1}Lynn Jr., why don't
you grab the Lilster,

08:01.480 --> 08:03.399
{\an1}and we'll find
a safer spot to hide.

08:03.482 --> 08:04.609
[monkey screams]

08:04.692 --> 08:07.069
[both screaming]

08:07.153 --> 08:08.738
{\an3}Looks like it's just
you and me, son.

08:08.821 --> 08:10.448
{\an3}What do you say we go hide
in the boiler room?

08:10.531 --> 08:11.657
Uh, wait, um,

08:11.741 --> 08:13.075
oh, the--the roof is next.

08:13.159 --> 08:14.285
{\an8}- "The roof is next"?

08:14.368 --> 08:15.620
{\an8}What does that mean?

08:15.703 --> 08:17.788
{\an7}And why did you
just look at your arm?

08:17.872 --> 08:21.000
{\an9}- What--I--

08:21.083 --> 08:22.335
{\an8}- "Room 2C, hallway, lobby,

08:22.418 --> 08:25.463
{\an8}Room 1A, laundry room."

08:25.546 --> 08:27.924
{\an9}These are all the places
we got pranked.

08:28.007 --> 08:30.885
{\an7}[gasps]
You've been helping her!

08:32.929 --> 08:34.388
{\an8}- Okay, I admit it!

08:34.472 --> 08:36.474
{\an7}I've been on Luan's scheme
the whole time.

08:36.557 --> 08:38.267
{\an8}A few weeks ago,
she came to me.

08:38.351 --> 08:39.559
{\an8}[whistling]

08:39.644 --> 08:41.102
{\an8}[screams]

08:41.187 --> 08:42.813
{\an8}<i>And said she needed</i>
<i>an inside man</i>

08:42.897 --> 08:45.191
{\an8}<i>to pull off her biggest</i>
<i>April Fool's ever.</i>

08:45.274 --> 08:47.068
{\an8}<i>It was a very</i>
<i>sophisticated operation.</i>

08:47.151 --> 08:48.861
{\an8}<i>First, we planted a fake ad</i>

08:48.945 --> 08:51.280
{\an8}<i>in one of Leni's magazines.</i>

08:51.364 --> 08:53.574
{\an8}<i>Then we set up</i>
<i>a fake clown camp.</i>

08:53.658 --> 08:55.451
{\an8}<i>Now, that wasn't as easy.</i>

08:55.534 --> 08:58.079
{\an8}<i>Do you have any idea</i>
<i>how much it costs to buy land?</i>

08:58.162 --> 08:59.789
<i>We faked the van breaking down</i>

08:59.872 --> 09:02.291
<i>with a little help</i>
<i>from one of Luna's fog machines.</i>

09:02.375 --> 09:04.794
<i>And, of course,</i>
<i>Luan wasn't gonna miss</i>

09:04.877 --> 09:06.629
<i>seeing you all get pranked.</i>

09:06.712 --> 09:08.631
<i>The manager--that's her.</i>

09:08.714 --> 09:10.466
<i>[exciting music]</i>

09:10.549 --> 09:13.010
<i>She's been watching everything</i>
<i>on the security cameras.</i>

09:13.094 --> 09:15.763
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:15.846 --> 09:18.849
- [cackling]

09:18.933 --> 09:20.643
{\an8}[cackling echoes]

09:20.726 --> 09:23.562
{\an9}- Dad, how could you sell out
your own family like that?

09:23.646 --> 09:25.189
{\an7}- Luan promised me
a prank-free decade.

09:25.273 --> 09:27.525
{\an8}A decade, son!

09:27.608 --> 09:29.402
{\an8}- I hope it was worth it.

09:29.485 --> 09:31.320
- Oh, it was not worth it.

09:31.404 --> 09:32.488
I feel terrible.

09:32.572 --> 09:33.990
What kind of father am I?

09:34.073 --> 09:36.993
What kind of...
[sobs] Husband?

09:37.076 --> 09:38.911
{\an8}[sobs]
- It's okay, Dad.

09:38.995 --> 09:41.747
{\an8}You're not the bad guy here.
Luan is.

09:41.831 --> 09:43.749
{\an8}- [sniffles]
No, no, son.

09:43.833 --> 09:45.001
{\an8}I'm just as guilty.

09:45.084 --> 09:46.502
{\an8}I went along with her.

09:46.586 --> 09:49.964
{\an7}But maybe it's not
too late to redeem myself.

09:50.047 --> 09:52.174
{\an7}What do you think of putting
Operation Find Our Family

09:52.258 --> 09:54.343
{\an7}and Get Back at Luan for Causing
Years of Emotional Damage

09:54.427 --> 09:57.346
{\an8}and Also Think of a Shorter Name
for This Operation into action?

09:57.430 --> 09:59.223
{\an9}- I'm in.

09:59.307 --> 10:01.350
<i>[elevator bell dings]</i>

10:01.434 --> 10:04.395
- My pranking is about
to reach new heights.

10:04.478 --> 10:06.689
[laughs] Get it?

10:06.772 --> 10:08.858
Oh, there's no one here.

10:08.941 --> 10:10.318
<i>[elevator clanks]</i>

10:10.401 --> 10:11.694
[buzzer sounds,
telephone rings]

10:11.777 --> 10:13.362
<i>- Hello, manager?</i>

10:13.446 --> 10:15.114
<i>This is Lynn Loud Sr.</i>

10:15.197 --> 10:17.575
<i>My son and I were just</i>
<i>headed up to the roof,</i>

10:17.658 --> 10:20.286
<i>but we seem to have</i>
<i>gotten stuck in the elevator.</i>

10:20.369 --> 10:22.872
- [deep voice]
Uh, I'll be right there.

10:22.955 --> 10:26.667
This is what I get
for hiring an amateur.

10:26.751 --> 10:28.210
That should do it.

10:28.294 --> 10:29.628
[elevator bell dings]

10:29.712 --> 10:30.713
[yells]

10:30.796 --> 10:31.964
{\an3}[grunts]

10:32.048 --> 10:34.216
[neon humming]

10:34.300 --> 10:36.010
[groans]

10:36.093 --> 10:37.261
Whoa!

10:37.345 --> 10:38.262
[groans]

10:38.346 --> 10:39.472
[splat]

10:41.265 --> 10:42.433
[monkey giggles]

10:44.310 --> 10:45.644
- We did it, you guys!

10:45.728 --> 10:47.813
We finally beat Luan
at her own game!

10:47.897 --> 10:48.773
[laughs]

10:48.856 --> 10:50.733
{\an8}[all cheering]

10:50.816 --> 10:53.194
- Clap, clap, clap.

10:53.277 --> 10:56.238
Well done, family.
You got me.

10:56.322 --> 10:58.115
You may have won this time,

10:58.199 --> 11:01.911
but next year I'm gonna
stop going easy on you

11:01.994 --> 11:05.456
and give you all an April Fool's
you'll never forget!

11:05.539 --> 11:07.249
Especially you, Dad!

11:07.333 --> 11:09.585
[cackling]

11:09.668 --> 11:11.045
- What have I done?

11:11.128 --> 11:12.254
[all screaming]

11:12.338 --> 11:15.549
- [continues cackling]

11:17.009 --> 11:19.970
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

11:20.054 --> 11:26.394
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:26.477 --> 11:28.729
{\an3}- Dad must have been
so caught up making us breakfast

11:28.813 --> 11:30.314
that he forgot his work stuff.

11:30.398 --> 11:32.733
{\an3}Luna, will you run
Dad's laptop up to him?

11:32.817 --> 11:34.944
- And leave my breakfast
sandwich with you animals?

11:35.027 --> 11:36.779
That's a neg, dude.

11:36.862 --> 11:38.906
{\an8}- I'll do it.
I trust you guys.

11:41.492 --> 11:44.286
- You guys, not cool.

11:44.370 --> 11:47.248
{\an1}As the oldest,
I totally get her sandwich.

11:47.331 --> 11:49.417
{\an1}- Hey, Dad, we saw you forgot
your laptop at home and--

11:49.500 --> 11:50.960
[keys clacking]

11:51.043 --> 11:54.463
{\an1}Oh, I can't believe
you get to have plastic surgery,

11:54.547 --> 11:56.757
{\an1}but I can't get
my belly button pierced?

11:56.841 --> 11:59.385
{\an3}- Uh, you must be looking
for Lynn Loud Sr.

11:59.468 --> 12:01.262
{\an3}I'm sorry, but he
doesn't work here anymore.

12:01.345 --> 12:02.805
{\an3}He's been gone
for three weeks.

12:02.888 --> 12:05.015
all: Three weeks?

12:05.099 --> 12:06.725
- Based on my calculations,

12:06.809 --> 12:09.437
{\an3}it appears our father's
employment was terminated

12:09.520 --> 12:11.689
{\an3}immediately following
the most recent

12:11.772 --> 12:13.732
Take Your Kids to Work Day.

12:13.816 --> 12:17.319
{\an8}- You don't think we had
anything to do with it, do you?

12:17.403 --> 12:19.321
{\an8}[laughter]

12:19.405 --> 12:20.906
{\an8}<i>[heavy rock music]</i>

12:20.990 --> 12:22.450
{\an8}- Whoo!

12:22.533 --> 12:24.201
{\an8}[kids groaning]
- We're literally the worst.

12:24.285 --> 12:27.580
{\an1}- Now I can't even eat
that delicious sandwich he made.

12:27.663 --> 12:29.081
I feel too guilty.

12:29.165 --> 12:31.417
{\an3}- [munching, swallows]
Me too.

12:31.500 --> 12:34.086
{\an9}- Wait, if Daddy hasn't
had a job for three weeks,

12:34.170 --> 12:37.006
{\an9}where's he even going when he
leaves the house every morning?

12:37.089 --> 12:39.008
{\an8}- I believe I can locate him.

12:39.091 --> 12:40.885
{\an8}I recently implanted
a tracking chip

12:40.968 --> 12:42.636
{\an8}in both our parental units.

12:42.720 --> 12:44.096
{\an8}- A tracking chip?

12:44.180 --> 12:45.890
{\an8}You didn't put those in us,
did you?

12:45.973 --> 12:47.475
{\an8}[device beeping]

12:48.767 --> 12:51.270
{\an8}- [wickedly] No.

12:51.353 --> 12:52.521
[device warbling, beeping]

12:52.605 --> 12:56.484
Lori, turn due southeast.

12:56.567 --> 12:58.527
{\an1}<i>We appear to have arrived</i>
<i>at Father's location.</i>

12:58.611 --> 13:00.821
- The Aloha Comrade

13:00.905 --> 13:03.365
{\an1}Hawaiian/Russian
fusion restaurant?

13:03.449 --> 13:04.867
What's he doing here?

13:04.950 --> 13:06.994
- Poor guy must be
drowning his sorrows

13:07.077 --> 13:10.706
in Humuhumunukunukuapua'a
borscht.

13:10.789 --> 13:12.708
all: What?

13:12.791 --> 13:15.544
- Have you guys really
never heard of borscht?

13:15.628 --> 13:17.880
- [humming]

13:17.963 --> 13:19.548
[tracker beeping]

13:19.632 --> 13:20.549
[kids gasp]

13:20.633 --> 13:23.219
- Dad's a dishwasher?

13:23.302 --> 13:25.221
- But he hates doing dishes.

13:25.304 --> 13:27.765
- Yeah, and now
that's his job--

13:27.848 --> 13:29.183
because of us.

13:29.266 --> 13:30.476
- This is worse than the time

13:30.559 --> 13:32.728
{\an1}we ruined his
40th birthday party.

13:32.811 --> 13:35.105
- And his college reunion.

13:35.189 --> 13:36.565
- And his roller dance
competition.

13:36.649 --> 13:39.401
- And his colonoscopy.

13:39.485 --> 13:42.112
- Guys, Dad does
so much for us,

13:42.196 --> 13:45.699
and all we do is
make his life worse.

13:45.783 --> 13:48.619
{\an3}- It's true.
We really need to fix this.

13:48.702 --> 13:50.162
{\an8}And I know how.

13:50.246 --> 13:52.706
{\an9}We're gonna get Dad
a new and better job.

13:52.790 --> 13:54.083
{\an8}- Yeah!
- Totally!

13:54.166 --> 13:55.084
{\an8}- We just all need
to work together!

13:57.503 --> 13:59.088
- Oh, guys, someone threw out

13:59.171 --> 14:01.590
a perfectly good
pineapple stroganoff.

14:01.674 --> 14:03.592
[munches]
Mmm.

14:06.095 --> 14:09.139
- [snaps fingers] I've got
the perfect job for Daddy--

14:09.223 --> 14:10.349
figure skater!

14:10.432 --> 14:11.392
[camera shutters clicking]

14:11.475 --> 14:13.310
{\an8}- No way!

14:13.394 --> 14:14.770
{\an8}Soccer goalie!

14:14.853 --> 14:17.773
- [grunting]

14:17.856 --> 14:19.942
{\an3}- Uh-uh.
Beat poet.

14:20.025 --> 14:21.944
- Darkness, despair...

14:22.027 --> 14:23.988
[plays bongos]
Lack of hair.

14:24.071 --> 14:25.573
{\an8}- May I remind you,

14:25.656 --> 14:28.284
{\an9}Father only has one
monetizable skill set--

14:28.367 --> 14:30.119
{\an8}information technology,

14:30.202 --> 14:32.246
{\an8}street name--IT.

14:32.329 --> 14:33.914
- Oh, what about this?

14:33.998 --> 14:36.041
"Computer expert needed
for Internet start-up."

14:36.125 --> 14:39.420
- I thought someone
already started the Internet.

14:39.503 --> 14:41.046
- This is good.

14:41.130 --> 14:42.965
Let's fill out an application
and send it in.

14:43.048 --> 14:44.174
And...done.

14:47.303 --> 14:48.429
[chimes]

14:49.638 --> 14:51.473
{\an7}- Yes!
They liked Dad's application

14:51.557 --> 14:53.350
{\an7}and want him to come in
for an interview!

14:53.434 --> 14:55.644
{\an9}- Wait, what if
he doesn't get the gig?

14:55.728 --> 14:57.980
{\an9}Then we'll have gotten
his hopes up for nothing.

14:58.063 --> 14:59.940
{\an7}- How about we
get the job for him,

15:00.024 --> 15:01.859
{\an8}then surprise him with it?

15:01.942 --> 15:04.570
{\an8}- So you're saying we clone
Dad while he's sleeping

15:04.653 --> 15:06.363
{\an8}and send the clone
to the interview?

15:06.447 --> 15:07.823
{\an8}Great idea!

15:07.906 --> 15:09.491
{\an8}I underestimated you,
Lincoln.

15:09.575 --> 15:11.577
{\an7}- Actually,
I was thinking one of us

15:11.660 --> 15:13.996
{\an7}could just put on this wig
and pretend to be Dad.

15:14.079 --> 15:17.124
{\an8}- Oh.
So I overestimated you.

15:17.207 --> 15:19.752
{\an7}- I know the perfect person
to play Dad.

15:19.835 --> 15:22.796
<i>[playful bluegrass music]</i>

15:22.880 --> 15:24.548
- So, Mr. Loud,

15:24.632 --> 15:26.175
why should we hire you?

15:26.258 --> 15:29.803
{\an1}- Because I've literally
mastered technology.

15:29.887 --> 15:31.555
[cell phone rings]

15:31.639 --> 15:32.723
Hi, boo-boo bear.

15:32.806 --> 15:34.516
Carol said what?

15:34.600 --> 15:36.935
Can I get some privacy?

15:37.019 --> 15:42.149
- You should hire me because
I'm responsible and mature.

15:42.232 --> 15:43.859
This tie is strangling me!

15:43.942 --> 15:46.528
Oh, I'm sweating in this suit.

15:46.612 --> 15:48.614
{\an1}These pants
are giving me a rash!

15:48.697 --> 15:50.741
{\an1}Ahh.
Now, where were we?

15:50.824 --> 15:52.868
{\an1}[thud]

15:52.951 --> 15:54.203
- Lynn Loud Sr.

15:54.286 --> 15:55.287
Pleased to meet you.

15:55.371 --> 15:56.372
[electricity crackles]

15:56.455 --> 15:58.082
What's the buzz around here?

15:58.165 --> 16:00.292
[laughs] Get it?

16:00.376 --> 16:01.502
{\an8}- Who are we kidding?

16:01.585 --> 16:03.212
{\an8}None of us can pull this off.

16:03.295 --> 16:06.173
{\an9}- There must be somebody
who can make a convincing Dad.

16:06.256 --> 16:09.718
{\an8}- Ooh, look at me,
I'm Lynn Loud Sr.

16:09.802 --> 16:14.348
{\an9}I can leave my trash bins out
as long as I want.

16:14.431 --> 16:17.685
- Mr. Grouse, could you
do us a small favor?

16:17.768 --> 16:19.395
- Hard pass.

16:19.478 --> 16:22.564
{\an3}- Wait, would a tray of my dad's
lasagna change your mind?

16:22.648 --> 16:25.109
{\an3}- No.

16:25.192 --> 16:28.362
{\an3}But two would.
[chuckles]

16:28.445 --> 16:29.196
Mmm, mmm!

16:31.490 --> 16:34.576
I'd like to be alone
with my lasagna.

16:34.660 --> 16:36.620
{\an1}- These are for later,
Mr. Grouse.

16:36.704 --> 16:38.247
{\an1}First, we need to
get you trained

16:38.330 --> 16:40.582
{\an1}so you'll fit
into the world of IT.

16:40.666 --> 16:44.294
- Ah, you kids
and your fancy abbreviations.

16:44.378 --> 16:46.630
In my day, we just said, "It."

16:46.714 --> 16:47.840
- Okay, Mr. Grouse.

16:47.923 --> 16:50.092
{\an1}Here's a laptop.
Boot it up.

16:50.175 --> 16:53.011
- Will you settle
for a penny loafer?

16:53.095 --> 16:54.596
{\an8}[whistle blows]
- No, no.

16:54.680 --> 16:55.848
{\an8}Not like that.

16:55.931 --> 16:56.765
{\an8}Like this.
[laptop chimes]

16:56.849 --> 16:58.684
- Okay, now open a window.

16:58.767 --> 17:01.228
- Eh, all right.

17:03.188 --> 17:04.940
{\an3}- [laughs]
Good one.

17:05.022 --> 17:06.108
{\an3}But wrong.

17:06.191 --> 17:07.859
{\an3}Like this.

17:07.943 --> 17:10.779
{\an9}- Now you need to empty
the trash on your computer.

17:10.863 --> 17:13.198
{\an8}- Eh, whatever you say.

17:13.281 --> 17:15.784
{\an8}- Yeah, I walked
right into that one.

17:15.867 --> 17:18.787
{\an8}<i>[rock music]</i>

17:18.871 --> 17:25.252
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:34.845 --> 17:35.888
- Yo, IT dude--

17:35.971 --> 17:39.183
I mean, how are you, sir?

17:39.266 --> 17:41.560
{\an3}My computer's acting
totally bogus--

17:41.643 --> 17:42.227
I-I mean broken.

17:42.311 --> 17:44.229
So, yeah, can you fix it?

17:44.313 --> 17:44.730
- Well, let's see.

17:44.813 --> 17:47.608
Have you rebooted?

17:47.691 --> 17:50.944
{\an1}Have you checked
your Wi-Fi connection?

17:51.028 --> 17:52.988
Oh, ah, it's clear as daylight.

17:53.071 --> 17:55.949
You need to update your drivers.

17:56.033 --> 17:57.743
{\an8}- I think he's ready.

17:57.826 --> 17:59.870
{\an9}- Almost.

18:00.746 --> 18:02.331
- It's been three hours.

18:02.414 --> 18:03.707
Where is he?

18:03.791 --> 18:05.250
- Passing
the Cluverius residence,

18:05.334 --> 18:07.002
about to make a right
onto Franklin.

18:07.086 --> 18:08.045
[device beeping]

18:08.128 --> 18:09.129
- How'd you know that?

18:09.213 --> 18:10.297
- Just a wild guess.

18:11.924 --> 18:15.803
- Oh, sorry, kids.

18:15.886 --> 18:18.138
Psych!
I got the job!

18:18.222 --> 18:20.015
[kids cheering]

18:20.098 --> 18:22.017
Now, if you'll excuse me,

18:22.100 --> 18:25.562
I have a date
with two hot dishes...

18:25.646 --> 18:28.482
of lasagna, for Pete's sake!

18:32.486 --> 18:34.029
all:
Good morning, Dad!

18:34.112 --> 18:35.989
{\an1}- Dang it.
What's going on, kids?

18:36.073 --> 18:37.950
- Get in.
We're driving you to work.

18:38.033 --> 18:39.326
- Uh, okay.

18:39.409 --> 18:40.828
{\an1}But there's something
I have to tell you.

18:40.911 --> 18:43.372
I have a new job now.

18:43.455 --> 18:45.499
- Yes, you do.

18:45.582 --> 18:47.167
[engine turning over]

18:47.251 --> 18:49.127
[engine revving]
- Oh, dang it!

18:49.211 --> 18:51.421
<i>[light music]</i>

18:51.505 --> 18:53.465
{\an1}Wait, this isn't
the Aloha Comrade.

18:53.549 --> 18:56.552
{\an3}- We know.
Say hello to your new office.

18:56.635 --> 18:58.387
- We felt bad
about getting you fired

18:58.470 --> 19:00.055
from your old IT job,

19:00.138 --> 19:01.723
so we got you a new one.

19:01.807 --> 19:04.768
{\an1}- Uh, guys, you didn't
get me fired from my old job.

19:04.852 --> 19:05.811
{\an1}I quit.

19:05.894 --> 19:06.979
- Why?

19:07.062 --> 19:09.231
So you could wash icky dishes?

19:09.314 --> 19:10.566
- Mm, not exactly.

19:10.649 --> 19:13.151
I'm training
to become a chef--

19:13.235 --> 19:14.528
my dream job!

19:14.611 --> 19:15.904
And washing dishes
is how you start.

19:15.988 --> 19:17.406
I didn't want to tell you guys

19:17.489 --> 19:18.574
until I passed
my training period.

19:18.657 --> 19:20.033
{\an8}all: Oh.

19:20.117 --> 19:22.786
{\an9}- It's the colonoscopy
all over again.

19:22.870 --> 19:24.788
{\an8}- It--it's okay, kids.
You meant well.

19:24.872 --> 19:26.248
{\an8}And now that you know,
you can just

19:26.331 --> 19:27.749
{\an8}take me back
to the restaurant.

19:27.833 --> 19:31.169
{\an8}- Uh, we kind of already
quit for you.

19:31.253 --> 19:33.046
- You listen to me, bub!

19:33.130 --> 19:35.757
No one makes my daddy
wash dishes!

19:35.841 --> 19:39.386
He's done with your stinky job
in your stinky restaurant!

19:39.469 --> 19:41.179
And another thing--

19:41.263 --> 19:42.431
[inhales deeply]

19:42.514 --> 19:45.475
[hair dryer whirring loudly]

19:46.351 --> 19:47.728
- Oh, dear.

19:47.811 --> 19:49.271
{\an8}<i>[bell dings]</i>
- Don't worry, Dad.

19:49.354 --> 19:51.189
{\an8}We'll talk your boss
into rehiring you.

19:51.273 --> 19:53.066
{\an8}- Yeah!
- To the Aloha Comrade!

19:53.150 --> 19:55.277
- Punch it, Lori!
- Wait!

19:55.360 --> 19:56.403
[gulping]

19:56.486 --> 19:57.571
<i>[rock music]</i>

19:57.654 --> 19:58.697
<i>Oh, that was hot.</i>

19:58.780 --> 19:59.865
[tires screech]

19:59.948 --> 20:00.991
- Oh, no!

20:01.074 --> 20:02.743
This is my last clean plate.

20:02.826 --> 20:04.119
{\an9}- Sir.

20:04.202 --> 20:05.913
{\an9}Please give our dad
his job back.

20:05.996 --> 20:07.748
{\an9}This was all
a misunderstanding.

20:07.831 --> 20:09.333
{\an7}- What is there
to misunderstanding?

20:09.416 --> 20:12.628
{\an8}First, I get the rudest
call of my life.

20:12.711 --> 20:15.422
{\an8}Then I have no one to help
with the breakfast rush.

20:15.505 --> 20:17.341
So my answer is <i> nyet.</i>

20:17.424 --> 20:18.675
- Yay!

20:18.759 --> 20:20.302
-<i> Nyet</i> means "no."

20:20.385 --> 20:21.386
- Aw.

20:21.470 --> 20:23.096
- Please don't punish our dad.

20:23.180 --> 20:24.473
This was our fault.

20:24.556 --> 20:26.808
{\an3}- Yeah, we're always
messing up.

20:26.892 --> 20:28.936
{\an3}- All we do is
make his life worse.

20:29.019 --> 20:31.396
{\an1}- Whoa, whoa, kids,
what are you talking about?

20:31.480 --> 20:34.149
{\an1}You make my life better
every day.

20:34.232 --> 20:35.484
This is just a job.

20:35.567 --> 20:37.027
{\an1}Don't worry.
I can find another one.

20:37.110 --> 20:38.654
<i>[tender music]</i>

20:38.737 --> 20:40.447
- [sniffling]

20:40.530 --> 20:43.283
I can't say <i> nyet</i> to a man
with such a nice family.

20:43.367 --> 20:44.743
You got your job back!

20:44.826 --> 20:45.661
{\an3}all: Yay!

20:45.744 --> 20:49.790
- Yes, my daddy's gonna
wash the dishes!

20:49.873 --> 20:52.334
[echoing]
<i>Dishes, dishes, dishes!</i>

20:52.417 --> 20:54.503
{\an1}- Ah, you!
Whoa! Ah!

20:54.586 --> 20:56.338
{\an1}[crash]
Ooh!

20:56.421 --> 20:58.340
Ow, my cooking arm.

20:58.423 --> 20:59.675
- Chef Sergei!

20:59.758 --> 21:02.594
{\an8}- Hmm, appears to be
a hairline fracture.

21:02.678 --> 21:04.012
{\an9}You'll need to
keep that immobilized

21:04.096 --> 21:06.807
{\an8}for at least three weeks.

21:06.890 --> 21:08.225
- I'm sorry, Lynn.

21:08.308 --> 21:09.893
I know I just
gave your job back,

21:09.977 --> 21:12.187
but I'm going to have to
shut down for a while.

21:12.270 --> 21:13.480
{\an3}- [sighs]

21:13.563 --> 21:15.899
<i>[bell dings]</i>
- Maybe not.

21:15.983 --> 21:18.860
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

21:18.944 --> 21:21.363
- OMgosh, you guys!

21:21.446 --> 21:23.115
The dining room is packed!

21:23.198 --> 21:26.743
- Everyone loves Dad's Kona
caviar breakfast sandwiches.

21:26.827 --> 21:28.245
- Mmm, Lynn,

21:28.328 --> 21:30.372
you don't need to train
to be a chef.

21:30.455 --> 21:32.040
You already are one!

21:32.124 --> 21:33.125
Forget about the dishwashing.

21:33.208 --> 21:36.086
I'm making you my co-chef.

21:36.169 --> 21:37.963
[kids cheering]

21:38.046 --> 21:39.756
Come with me.

21:39.840 --> 21:42.884
I want the customers to know
who made this delicious meal.

21:42.968 --> 21:46.972
{\an1}- Ooh, Sergei didn't finish
his breakfast sandwich.

21:47.055 --> 21:47.973
all: Dibs!

21:48.056 --> 21:51.601
[keys clacking]

21:51.685 --> 21:53.687
- There you go, all fixed!

21:53.770 --> 21:55.063
- Uh, great, thanks.

21:55.147 --> 21:55.897
Could you log out for me?

21:55.981 --> 21:58.025
{\an3}- Sure.

21:58.108 --> 22:00.652
{\an3}[grunts]
Good thing I brought a log.

22:02.738 --> 22:03.613
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:03.697 --> 22:06.324
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:06.408 --> 22:08.910
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud House ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud House ♪</i>

22:08.994 --> 22:11.371
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:11.455 --> 22:15.333
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show</i>
<i>our love in the Loud House ♪</i>

22:15.417 --> 22:16.918
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Loud House ♪</i>

22:17.002 --> 22:18.587
